.TH "ib_alloc_mr_integrity" 9 "ib_alloc_mr_integrity" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ib_alloc_mr_integrity \- Allocates an integrity memory region
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ib_mr *" ib_alloc_mr_integrity
.BI "(struct ib_pd *pd "  ","
.BI "u32 max_num_data_sg "  ","
.BI "u32 max_num_meta_sg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pd" 12
protection domain associated with the region
.IP "max_num_data_sg" 12
maximum data sg entries available for registration
.IP "max_num_meta_sg" 12
maximum metadata sg entries available for
registration
.SH "NOTES"
Memory registration page/sg lists must not exceed max_num_sg,
also the integrity page/sg lists must not exceed max_num_meta_sg.
